title: Wolf Pack golf has best showing; Khoo in second for women
text:
Wolf Pack golf has best showing; Khoo in second for women Staff report 10:47 p.m. PDT October 6, 2015 Nevada athletics 

BOOTH LEADS PACK MEN’S GOLF TO BEST FINISH OF SEASON 
FRESNO — Grant Booth capped a strong tournament with his third straight round in the 60s on Tuesday as his 68 propelled the sophomore to a tie for sixth place at the Nick Watney Invitational. 
Booth led Nevada to a fifth-place finish overall, the best tournament of the year so far for the Nevada men. 
Sophomore Jooho Lee closed with a 68 to tie for 24th. Freshman Travis Fredborg and junior Nick Fuller tied for 34th while sophomore Corey Eddings took 58th. David Hinitz, competing as an individual, was 79th. 
KHOO A SHOT BACK WITH 18 TO PLAY AT AGGIE INVITATIONAL 
LAS CRUCES, N.M. — Nevada senior Caryn Khoo is one shot back at the Aggie Invitational heading into Wednesday’s final round. 
Khoo, who opened with a 69 on Monday, hit a 71 on Tuesday at New Mexico State Golf Course. That pushed her up one spot to a tie for second place along with BYU’s Kendra Dalton. Khoo and Dalton are 4 under for the tournament. 
Nevada is in sixth place overall. Read or Share this story: http://on.rgj.com/1Lhb5Fr TOP VIDEOS
